68// Make these non-inline because of std::unique_ptr. See comment in
69// codegen_llvm.cc for more information.
70CodeGenCPU::CodeGenCPU() = default;
71CodeGenCPU::~CodeGenCPU() = default;

73void CodeGenCPU::Init(const std::string& module_name, LLVMTarget* llvm_target, bool system_lib,
74 bool dynamic_lookup, bool target_c_runtime) {
75 CodeGenLLVM::Init(module_name, llvm_target, system_lib, dynamic_lookup, target_c_runtime);
76 dbg_info_ = CreateDebugInfo(module_.get());
77 static_assert(sizeof(TVMValue) == sizeof(double), "invariant");
78 func_handle_map_.clear();
79 export_system_symbols_.clear();
80
81 // Runtime types.
82
83 t_tvm_shape_index_ =
84 llvm::Type::getIntNTy(*llvm_target_->GetContext(), DataType::ShapeIndex().bits());
85 // Defined in 3rdparty/dlpack/include/dlpack/dlpack.h:
86 // typedef struct { DLDeviceType device_type; int device_id; } DLDevice;
87 t_tvm_device_ = llvm::StructType::create({t_int_, t_int_});
88 // Defined in 3rdparty/dlpack/include/dlpack/dlpack.h:
89 // typedef struct { uint8_t code; uint8_t bits; uint16_t lanes; } DLDataType;
90 t_tvm_type_ = llvm::StructType::create({t_int8_, t_int8_, t_int16_});
91 // Defined in include/tvm/runtime/c_runtime_api.h:
92 // typedef void* TVMFunctionHandle;
93 t_tvm_func_handle_ = t_void_p_;
94 // Defined in 3rdparty/dlpack/include/dlpack/dlpack.h:
95 // typedef struct { ... } DLTensor;
96 t_tvm_array_ = llvm::StructType::create({t_void_p_, t_tvm_device_, t_int_, t_tvm_type_,
97 t_tvm_shape_index_->getPointerTo(),
98 t_tvm_shape_index_->getPointerTo(), t_int64_});
99 // Defined in include/tvm/runtime/c_runtime_api.h:
100 // typedef union { ... } TVMValue;
101 t_tvm_value_ = llvm::StructType::create({t_float64_});
102 // Defined in include/tvm/runtime/c_backend_api.h:
103 // typedef struct { void* sync_handle; int32_t num_task; } TVMParallelGroupEnv;
104 t_tvm_parallel_group_env_ = llvm::StructType::create({t_int32_->getPointerTo(), t_int32_});
105 // Defined in include/tvm/runtime/c_backend_api.h:
106 // typedef int (*TVMBackendPackedCFunc)(TVMValue* args, int* type_codes, int num_args,
107 // TVMValue* out_ret_value, int* out_ret_tcode,
108 // void* resource_handle);
109 ftype_tvm_backend_packed_c_func_ = llvm::FunctionType::get(
110 t_int_,
111 {t_void_p_, t_int_->getPointerTo(), t_int_, t_void_p_, t_int_->getPointerTo(), t_void_p_},
112 false);
113 t_tvm_crt_func_registry_ = llvm::StructType::create(
114 {t_char_->getPointerTo(), ftype_tvm_backend_packed_c_func_->getPointerTo()});
115 t_tvm_crt_module_ = llvm::StructType::create({t_tvm_crt_func_registry_->getPointerTo()});
116 // Defined in include/tvm/runtime/c_backend_api.h:
117 // typedef int (*FTVMParallelLambda)(int task_id, TVMParallelGroupEnv* penv, void* cdata);
118 ftype_tvm_parallel_lambda_ = llvm::FunctionType::get(
119 t_int_, {t_int_, t_tvm_parallel_group_env_->getPointerTo(), t_void_p_}, false);
120 md_tbaa_ctx_ptr_ = md_builder_->createTBAAScalarTypeNode("ctx_ptr", md_tbaa_root_);
121
122 // Runtime functions.
123
124 // Defined in include/tvm/runtime/c_runtime_api.h:
125 // int TVMFuncCall(TVMFunctionHandle func, TVMValue* arg_values, int* type_codes, int num_args,
126 // TVMValue* ret_val, int* ret_type_code);
127 ftype_tvm_func_call_ = llvm::FunctionType::get(
128 t_int_,
129 {t_tvm_func_handle_, t_tvm_value_->getPointerTo(), t_int_->getPointerTo(), t_int_,
130 t_tvm_value_->getPointerTo(), t_int_->getPointerTo()},
131 false);
132 // Defined in include/tvm/runtime/c_backend_api.h:
133 // int TVMBackendGetFuncFromEnv(void* mod_node, const char* func_name, TVMFunctionHandle* out);
134 ftype_tvm_get_func_from_env_ = llvm::FunctionType::get(
135 t_int_, {t_void_p_, t_char_->getPointerTo(), t_tvm_func_handle_->getPointerTo()}, false);
136 // Defined in include/tvm/runtime/c_runtime_api.h:
137 // void TVMAPISetLastError(const char* msg);
138 ftype_tvm_api_set_last_error_ =
139 llvm::FunctionType::get(t_void_, {t_char_->getPointerTo()}, false);
140 // Defined in include/tvm/runtime/c_backend_api.h:
141 // int TVMBackendParallelLaunch(FTVMParallelLambda flambda, void* cdata, int num_task);
142 ftype_tvm_parallel_launch_ = llvm::FunctionType::get(
143 t_int_, {ftype_tvm_parallel_lambda_->getPointerTo(), t_void_p_, t_int_}, false);
144 // Defined in include/tvm/runtime/c_backend_api.h:
145 // int TVMBackendParallelBarrier(int task_id, TVMParallelGroupEnv* penv);
146 ftype_tvm_parallel_barrier_ =
147 llvm::FunctionType::get(t_int_, {t_int_, t_tvm_parallel_group_env_->getPointerTo()}, false);
148 ftype_tvm_static_init_callback_ = llvm::FunctionType::get(t_int_, {t_void_p_}, false);
149 ftype_tvm_static_init_ =
150 llvm::FunctionType::get(t_int_,
151 {t_void_p_->getPointerTo(),
152 ftype_tvm_static_init_callback_->getPointerTo(), t_void_p_, t_int_},
153 false);
154 // initialize TVM runtime API
155 if (system_lib && !target_c_runtime) {
156 // We will need this in environment for backward registration.
157 // Defined in include/tvm/runtime/c_backend_api.h:
158 // int TVMBackendRegisterSystemLibSymbol(const char* name, void* ptr);
159 f_tvm_register_system_symbol_ = llvm::Function::Create(
160 llvm::FunctionType::get(t_int_, {t_char_->getPointerTo(), t_void_p_}, false),
161 llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage, "TVMBackendRegisterSystemLibSymbol", module_.get());
162 } else {
163 f_tvm_register_system_symbol_ = nullptr;
164 }
165 if (dynamic_lookup || system_lib) {
166 f_tvm_func_call_ = llvm::Function::Create(ftype_tvm_func_call_, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
167 "TVMFuncCall", module_.get());
168 f_tvm_get_func_from_env_ =
169 llvm::Function::Create(ftype_tvm_get_func_from_env_, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
170 "TVMBackendGetFuncFromEnv", module_.get());
171 f_tvm_api_set_last_error_ =
172 llvm::Function::Create(ftype_tvm_api_set_last_error_, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
173 "TVMAPISetLastError", module_.get());
174 f_tvm_parallel_launch_ =
175 llvm::Function::Create(ftype_tvm_parallel_launch_, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
176 "TVMBackendParallelLaunch", module_.get());
177 f_tvm_parallel_barrier_ =
178 llvm::Function::Create(ftype_tvm_parallel_barrier_, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
179 "TVMBackendParallelBarrier", module_.get());
180 }
181 target_c_runtime_ = target_c_runtime;
182 is_system_lib_ = system_lib;
183 InitGlobalContext(dynamic_lookup);
184}
185
186void CodeGenCPU::AddFunction(const PrimFunc& f) {
187 CodeGenLLVM::AddFunction(f);
188 if (f_tvm_register_system_symbol_ != nullptr) {
189 auto global_symbol = f->GetAttr<String>(tvm::attr::kGlobalSymbol);
190 ICHECK(global_symbol.defined())
191 << "CodeGenLLVM: Expect PrimFunc to have the global_symbol attribute";
192 export_system_symbols_.emplace_back(
193 std::make_pair(global_symbol.value().operator std::string(), function_));
194 }
195 AddDebugInformation(f, function_);
196}
197
198// Following Glow |DebugInfo::generateFunctionDebugInfo|, https://git.io/fjadv
199void CodeGenCPU::AddDebugInformation(PrimFunc f_tir, llvm::Function* f_llvm) {
200#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 50
201 ICHECK(!f_llvm->getSubprogram());
202 llvm::SmallVector<llvm::Metadata*, 4> paramTys;
203 // Functions in TIR can only return void or an int.
204 ICHECK(f_llvm->getReturnType() == t_void_ || f_llvm->getReturnType() == t_int_)
205 << "Unexpected return type";
206 auto ret_type_tir = f_llvm->getReturnType() == t_int_ ? DataType::Int(32) : DataType::Void();
207 llvm::DIType* returnTy =
208 GetDebugType(GetTypeFromRuntimeDataType(ret_type_tir), f_llvm->getReturnType());
209 paramTys.push_back(returnTy);
210 for (size_t i = 0; i < f_llvm->arg_size(); ++i) {
211 paramTys.push_back(
212 GetDebugType(GetType(f_tir->params[i]), f_llvm->getFunctionType()->getParamType(i)));
213 }
214 auto* DIFunctionTy = dbg_info_->di_builder_->createSubroutineType(
215 dbg_info_->di_builder_->getOrCreateTypeArray(paramTys));
216
217 bool local_to_unit = llvm::GlobalValue::isLocalLinkage(f_llvm->getLinkage());
218
219#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 80
220 auto SPFlags =
221 llvm::DISubprogram::toSPFlags(local_to_unit, /*IsDefinition=*/true, /*IsOptimized=*/true);
222 auto* DIFunction = dbg_info_->di_builder_->createFunction(
223 /*Scope=*/dbg_info_->file_, /*Name=*/f_llvm->getName(), /*LinkageName=*/"",
224 /*File=*/dbg_info_->file_, /*LineNo=*/0, /*Ty=*/DIFunctionTy,
225 /*ScopeLine=*/0, /*Flags=*/llvm::DINode::FlagZero, /*SPFlags=*/SPFlags);
226#else
227 auto* DIFunction = dbg_info_->di_builder_->createFunction(
228 /*Scope=*/dbg_info_->file_, /*Name=*/f_llvm->getName(), /*LinkageName=*/"",
229 /*File=*/dbg_info_->file_, /*LineNo=*/0, /*Ty=*/DIFunctionTy,
230 /*isLocalToUnit=*/local_to_unit, /*isDefinition=*/true, /*ScopeLine=*/0,
231 /*Flags=*/llvm::DINode::FlagPrototyped, /*isOptimized=*/true);
232#endif
233
234 ICHECK(DIFunction);
235 f_llvm->setSubprogram(DIFunction);
236 ICHECK_EQ(f_llvm->getSubprogram(), DIFunction);
237
238 IRBuilder builder(&f_llvm->getEntryBlock());
239 if (!f_llvm->getEntryBlock().empty()) {
240 builder.SetInsertPoint(&f_llvm->getEntryBlock().front());
241 }
242 llvm::DebugLoc DL;
243 builder.SetCurrentDebugLocation(DL);
244 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
245 for (size_t i = 0; i < f_llvm->arg_size(); ++i) {
246 auto* paramAlloca = builder.CreateAlloca(f_llvm->getFunctionType()->getParamType(i));
247 std::string paramName = "arg" + std::to_string(i + 1);
248 auto param = dbg_info_->di_builder_->createParameterVariable(
249 DIFunction, paramName, i + 1, dbg_info_->file_, 0,
250 GetDebugType(GetType(f_tir->params[i]), f_llvm->getFunctionType()->getParamType(i)),
251 /*alwaysPreserve=*/true);
252 auto* store = builder.CreateStore(f_llvm->arg_begin() + i, paramAlloca);
253 auto* di_loc = llvm::DILocation::get(*ctx, 0, 0, DIFunction);
254 dbg_info_->di_builder_->insertDeclare(paramAlloca, param,
255 dbg_info_->di_builder_->createExpression(),
256 llvm::DebugLoc(di_loc), store);
257 }
258 dbg_info_->di_builder_->finalizeSubprogram(f_llvm->getSubprogram());
259 auto* scope = f_llvm->getSubprogram();
260 if (!scope) {
261 return;
262 }
263 for (auto& BB : *f_llvm) {
264 for (auto& I : BB) {
265 if (I.getDebugLoc()) {
266 continue;
267 }
268 auto* di_loc = llvm::DILocation::get(*ctx, 0, 0, scope);
269 I.setDebugLoc(llvm::DebugLoc(di_loc));
270 }
271 }
272#endif
273}
274
275llvm::DIType* CodeGenCPU::GetDebugType(const Type& ty_tir, llvm::Type* ty_llvm) {
276 if (ty_llvm == t_void_) {
277 return nullptr;
278 } else if (ty_llvm == llvm::Type::getFloatTy(*llvm_target_->GetContext())) {
279 return dbg_info_->di_builder_->createBasicType("float", 32, llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_float);
280 } else if (ty_llvm == t_int8_) {
281 return dbg_info_->di_builder_->createBasicType("int8", 8, llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_signed);
282 } else if (ty_llvm == t_int32_) {
283 return dbg_info_->di_builder_->createBasicType("int32", 32, llvm::dwarf::DW_ATE_signed);
284 } else if (ty_llvm->isPointerTy()) {
285 auto* ptr_type = ty_tir.as<PointerTypeNode>();
286 ICHECK(ptr_type != nullptr || GetRuntimeDataType(ty_tir).is_handle())
287 << "Got LLVM pointer type from non-pointer IR type: " << ty_tir;
288 auto* pointee_type = ptr_type != nullptr ? GetDebugType(ptr_type->element_type,
289 GetLLVMType(ptr_type->element_type))
290 : nullptr;
291 return dbg_info_->di_builder_->createPointerType(pointee_type,
292 ty_llvm->getPrimitiveSizeInBits());
293 } else {
294 std::string type_str;
295 llvm::raw_string_ostream rso(type_str);
296 ty_llvm->print(rso);
297 LOG(FATAL) << "Unknown LLVM type:" << rso.str();
298 }
299 return nullptr;
300}
301
302void CodeGenCPU::AddMainFunction(const std::string& entry_func_name) {
303 llvm::Function* f = module_->getFunction(entry_func_name);
304 ICHECK(f) << "Function " << entry_func_name << "does not in module";
305 llvm::Type* type = llvm::ArrayType::get(t_char_, entry_func_name.length() + 1);
306 llvm::GlobalVariable* global =
307 new llvm::GlobalVariable(*module_, type, true, llvm::GlobalValue::WeakAnyLinkage, nullptr,
308 runtime::symbol::tvm_module_main);
309#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 100
310 global->setAlignment(llvm::Align(1));
311#else
312 global->setAlignment(1);
313#endif
314 // comdat is needed for windows select any linking to work
315 // set comdat to Any(weak linking)
316 if (llvm_target_->GetOrCreateTargetMachine()->getTargetTriple().isOSWindows()) {
317 llvm::Comdat* comdat = module_->getOrInsertComdat(runtime::symbol::tvm_module_main);
318 comdat->setSelectionKind(llvm::Comdat::Any);
319 global->setComdat(comdat);
320 }
321
322 global->setInitializer(
323 llvm::ConstantDataArray::getString(*llvm_target_->GetContext(), entry_func_name));
324 global->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalVariable::DLLExportStorageClass);
325}
326
327std::unique_ptr<llvm::Module> CodeGenCPU::Finish() {
328 // link modules
329 if (dbg_info_ != nullptr) {
330 dbg_info_->di_builder_->finalize();
331 }
332 return CodeGenLLVM::Finish();
333}
334
335CodeGenLLVM::TypedPointer CodeGenCPU::CreateStructRefPtr(DataType t, llvm::Value* buf,
336 llvm::Value* index, int kind) {
337 if (kind < builtin::kArrKindBound_) {
338 if (buf->getType() == t_void_p_) {
339 buf = builder_->CreatePointerCast(buf, t_tvm_array_->getPointerTo());
340 } else {
341 ICHECK_EQ(buf->getType(), t_tvm_array_->getPointerTo());
342 }
343 }
344 switch (kind) {
345 case builtin::kArrAddr: {
346 return TypedPointer(t_tvm_array_, builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_tvm_array_, buf, index));
347 }
348 case builtin::kArrData: {
349 llvm::Type* member_type = t_tvm_array_->getStructElementType(0);
350 llvm::Value* member_addr =
351 builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_tvm_array_, buf, {index, ConstInt32(0)});
352 return TypedPointer(member_type, member_addr);
353 }
354 case builtin::kArrShape: {
355 llvm::Type* member_type = t_tvm_array_->getStructElementType(4);
356 llvm::Value* member_addr =
357 builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_tvm_array_, buf, {index, ConstInt32(4)});
358 return TypedPointer(member_type, member_addr);
359 }
360 case builtin::kArrStrides: {
361 llvm::Type* member_type = t_tvm_array_->getStructElementType(5);
362 llvm::Value* member_addr =
363 builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_tvm_array_, buf, {index, ConstInt32(5)});
364 return TypedPointer(member_type, member_addr);
365 }
366 case builtin::kArrNDim: {
367 llvm::Type* member_type = t_tvm_array_->getStructElementType(2);
368 llvm::Value* member_addr =
369 builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_tvm_array_, buf, {index, ConstInt32(2)});
370 return TypedPointer(member_type, member_addr);
371 }
372 case builtin::kArrTypeCode: {
373 llvm::Type* member_type = t_tvm_array_->getStructElementType(3)->getStructElementType(0);
374 llvm::Value* member_addr =
375 builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_tvm_array_, buf, {index, ConstInt32(3), ConstInt32(0)});
376 return TypedPointer(member_type, member_addr);
377 }
378 case builtin::kArrTypeBits: {
379 llvm::Type* member_type = t_tvm_array_->getStructElementType(3)->getStructElementType(1);
380 llvm::Value* member_addr =
381 builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_tvm_array_, buf, {index, ConstInt32(3), ConstInt32(1)});
382 return TypedPointer(member_type, member_addr);
383 }
384 case builtin::kArrTypeLanes: {
385 llvm::Type* member_type = t_tvm_array_->getStructElementType(3)->getStructElementType(2);
386 llvm::Value* member_addr =
387 builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_tvm_array_, buf, {index, ConstInt32(3), ConstInt32(2)});
388 return TypedPointer(member_type, member_addr);
389 }
390 case builtin::kArrByteOffset: {
391 llvm::Type* member_type = t_tvm_array_->getStructElementType(6);
392 llvm::Value* member_addr =
393 builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_tvm_array_, buf, {index, ConstInt32(6)});
394 return TypedPointer(member_type, member_addr);
395 }
396 case builtin::kArrDeviceId: {
397 llvm::Type* member_type = t_tvm_array_->getStructElementType(1)->getStructElementType(1);
398 llvm::Value* member_addr =
399 builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_tvm_array_, buf, {index, ConstInt32(1), ConstInt32(1)});
400 return TypedPointer(member_type, member_addr);
401 }
402 case builtin::kArrDeviceType: {
403 llvm::Type* member_type = t_tvm_array_->getStructElementType(1)->getStructElementType(0);
404 llvm::Value* member_addr =
405 builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_tvm_array_, buf, {index, ConstInt32(1), ConstInt32(0)});
406 return TypedPointer(member_type, member_addr);
407 }
408 case builtin::kTVMValueContent: {
409 ICHECK_EQ(t.lanes(), 1);
410 ICHECK(t.is_handle() || t.bits() == 64);
411 if (t.is_int()) {
412 buf = builder_->CreatePointerCast(buf, t_int64_->getPointerTo());
413 return TypedPointer(t_int64_, builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_int64_, buf, index));
414 } else if (t.is_float()) {
415 buf = builder_->CreatePointerCast(buf, t_float64_->getPointerTo());
416 return TypedPointer(t_float64_, builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_float64_, buf, index));
417 } else {
418 ICHECK(t.is_handle());
419 buf = builder_->CreatePointerCast(buf, t_tvm_value_->getPointerTo());
420 buf = builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_tvm_value_, buf, index);
421 return TypedPointer(t_void_p_, builder_->CreatePointerCast(buf, t_void_p_->getPointerTo()));
422 }
423 }
424 default:
425 LOG(FATAL) << "unknown field code";
426 return TypedPointer();
427 }
428}
429
430llvm::Value* CodeGenCPU::CreateCallExtern(Type ret_type, String global_symbol,
431 const Array<PrimExpr>& args, bool skip_first_arg) {
432 std::vector<llvm::Value*> arg_values;
433 for (size_t i = static_cast<size_t>(skip_first_arg); i < args.size(); ++i) {
434 arg_values.push_back(MakeValue(args[i]));
435 }
436 std::vector<llvm::Type*> arg_types;
437 for (llvm::Value* v : arg_values) {
438 arg_types.push_back(v->getType());
439 }
440 llvm::FunctionType* ftype = llvm::FunctionType::get(GetLLVMType(ret_type), arg_types, false);
441 // Check if it is available in global function table as injected function.
442 auto it = gv_func_map_.find(global_symbol);
443 if (it != gv_func_map_.end()) {
444 if (it->second == nullptr) {
445 gv_func_map_[global_symbol] = InitContextPtr(ftype->getPointerTo(), "__" + global_symbol);
446 it = gv_func_map_.find(global_symbol);
447 }
448#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 90
449 auto ext_callee = llvm::FunctionCallee(ftype, GetContextPtr(it->second));
450#else
451 auto ext_callee = GetContextPtr(it->second);
452#endif
453 return builder_->CreateCall(ext_callee, arg_values);
454 } else {
455 llvm::Function* f = module_->getFunction(MakeStringRef(global_symbol));
456 if (f == nullptr) {
457 f = llvm::Function::Create(ftype, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
458 MakeStringRef(global_symbol), module_.get());
459 }
460#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 90
461 auto ext_callee = llvm::FunctionCallee(f);
462#else
463 auto ext_callee = f;
464#endif
465 return builder_->CreateCall(ext_callee, arg_values);
466 }
467}
468
469llvm::GlobalVariable* CodeGenCPU::InitContextPtr(llvm::Type* p_type, std::string name) {
470 llvm::GlobalVariable* gv = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
471 *module_, p_type, false, llvm::GlobalValue::LinkOnceAnyLinkage, nullptr, name);
472#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 100
473 gv->setAlignment(llvm::Align(data_layout_->getTypeAllocSize(p_type)));
474#else
475 gv->setAlignment(data_layout_->getTypeAllocSize(p_type));
476#endif
477 gv->setInitializer(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(p_type));
478 gv->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLStorageClassTypes::DLLExportStorageClass);
479 // comdat is needed for windows select any linking to work
480 // set comdat to Any(weak linking)
481 if (llvm_target_->GetOrCreateTargetMachine()->getTargetTriple().isOSWindows()) {
482 llvm::Comdat* comdat = module_->getOrInsertComdat(name);
483 comdat->setSelectionKind(llvm::Comdat::Any);
484 gv->setComdat(comdat);
485 }
486 return gv;
487}
488
489llvm::Value* CodeGenCPU::GetContextPtr(llvm::GlobalVariable* gv) {
490 ICHECK(gv != nullptr);
491#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
492 llvm::LoadInst* faddr =
493 builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(gv->getValueType(), gv, llvm::Align(gv->getAlignment()));
494#elif TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 80
495 llvm::LoadInst* faddr = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(gv->getValueType(), gv, gv->getAlignment());
496#else
497 llvm::LoadInst* faddr = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(gv, gv->getAlignment());
498#endif
499 faddr->setMetadata("tbaa",
500 md_builder_->createTBAAStructTagNode(md_tbaa_ctx_ptr_, md_tbaa_ctx_ptr_, 0));
501 return faddr;
502}
503
504void CodeGenCPU::InitGlobalContext(bool dynamic_lookup) {
505 // Module context
506 gv_mod_ctx_ = InitContextPtr(t_void_p_, tvm::runtime::symbol::tvm_module_ctx);
507 // Register back the locations.
508 if (f_tvm_register_system_symbol_ != nullptr && !target_c_runtime_) {
509 export_system_symbols_.emplace_back(
510 std::make_pair(tvm::runtime::symbol::tvm_module_ctx, gv_mod_ctx_));
511 } else {
512 if (!dynamic_lookup) {
513 gv_tvm_func_call_ = InitContextPtr(ftype_tvm_func_call_->getPointerTo(), "__TVMFuncCall");
514 gv_tvm_get_func_from_env_ = InitContextPtr(ftype_tvm_get_func_from_env_->getPointerTo(),
515 "__TVMBackendGetFuncFromEnv");
516 gv_tvm_api_set_last_error_ =
517 InitContextPtr(ftype_tvm_api_set_last_error_->getPointerTo(), "__TVMAPISetLastError");
518 gv_tvm_parallel_launch_ =
519 InitContextPtr(ftype_tvm_parallel_launch_->getPointerTo(), "__TVMBackendParallelLaunch");
520 gv_tvm_parallel_barrier_ = InitContextPtr(ftype_tvm_parallel_barrier_->getPointerTo(),
521 "__TVMBackendParallelBarrier");
522 // Mark as context functions
523 gv_func_map_["TVMBackendAllocWorkspace"] = nullptr;
524 gv_func_map_["TVMBackendFreeWorkspace"] = nullptr;
525 }
526 }
527}
528
529llvm::BasicBlock* CodeGenCPU::CheckCallSuccess(llvm::Value* retcode) {
530 // create emit codes that checks and load the function.
531 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
532 auto* fail_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "call_fail", function_);
533 auto* end_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "call_end", function_);
534 auto* succ = builder_->CreateICmpEQ(retcode, llvm::ConstantInt::get(t_int_, 0));
535 builder_->CreateCondBr(succ, end_block, fail_block, md_very_likely_branch_);
536 builder_->SetInsertPoint(fail_block);
537 // return the code.
538 builder_->CreateRet(retcode);
539 // otherwise set it to be new end.
540 builder_->SetInsertPoint(end_block);
541 return end_block;
542}
543
544void CodeGenCPU::CreateComputeScope(const AttrStmtNode* op) {
545 /*! \brief maintain states that should be guarded when step into compute scope */
546 struct ComputeScopeStates {
547 explicit ComputeScopeStates(CodeGenCPU* parent) : parent_(parent) {}
548
549 void EnterWithScope() {
550 std::swap(function_, parent_->function_);
551 std::swap(analyzer_, parent_->analyzer_);
552 std::swap(var_map_, parent_->var_map_);
553 }
554
555 void ExitWithScope() {
556 std::swap(function_, parent_->function_);
557 std::swap(analyzer_, parent_->analyzer_);
558 std::swap(var_map_, parent_->var_map_);
559 }
560
561 llvm::Function* function_{nullptr};
562 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, llvm::Value*> var_map_;
563 std::unique_ptr<arith::Analyzer> analyzer_{std::make_unique<arith::Analyzer>()};
564 CodeGenCPU* parent_;
565 };
566
567 // There are two reasons why we create another function for compute_scope
568 // - Make sure the generated compute function is clearly separately(though it can get inlined)
569 // - Set noalias on all the pointer arguments, some of them are loaded from TVMArgs.
570 // This is easier than set the alias scope manually.
571 Array<Var> vargs = tir::UndefinedVars(op->body, {});
572 std::vector<llvm::Value*> arg_values;
573 std::vector<llvm::Type*> arg_types;
574 for (Var v : vargs) {
575 llvm::Value* value = MakeValue(v);
576 value->setName(v->name_hint.c_str());
577 arg_values.push_back(value);
578 arg_types.push_back(value->getType());
579 }
580 llvm::FunctionType* ftype = llvm::FunctionType::get(t_int_, arg_types, false);
581 // $xxx_compute_ functions are not global. They should be marked as static (via InternalLinkage)
582 // to call them correctly on MIPS platform (CALL16 issue)
583 // Linkage ld Error: CALL16 reloc at 0x290 not against global symbol
584 const StringImmNode* value = op->value.as<StringImmNode>();
585 ICHECK(value != nullptr);
586 llvm::Function* fcompute = llvm::Function::Create(ftype, llvm::Function::InternalLinkage,
587 MakeStringRef(value->value), module_.get());
588 SetTargetAttributes(fcompute);
589
590 llvm::BasicBlock* compute_call_end = CheckCallSuccess(builder_->CreateCall(fcompute, arg_values));
591 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
592 // enter compute scope and setup compute function.
593 With<ComputeScopeStates> scope_states_guard(this);
594 size_t idx = 0;
595 for (auto it = fcompute->arg_begin(); it != fcompute->arg_end(); ++it, ++idx) {
596 llvm::Argument* v = &(*it);
597 const Var& var = vargs[idx];
598 var_map_[var.get()] = v;
599 if (var.dtype().is_handle() && !alias_var_set_.count(var.get())) {
600 // set non alias.
601#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 50
602 fcompute->addParamAttr(idx, llvm::Attribute::NoAlias);
603 // always not inline compute function to make the code structure clean
604#else
605 fcompute->setDoesNotAlias(idx + 1);
606#endif
607 fcompute->addFnAttr(llvm::Attribute::NoInline);
608 }
609 // Add alignment attribute if needed.
610#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 50
611 auto f = alloc_storage_info_.find(var.get());
612 if (f != alloc_storage_info_.end()) {
613 unsigned align = f->second.alignment;
614 if (align > 1) {
615 auto attr = llvm::Attribute::get(*ctx, llvm::Attribute::Alignment, align);
616 fcompute->addParamAttr(idx, attr);
617 }
618 }
619#endif
620 }
621
622 function_ = fcompute;
623 auto* compute_entry = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "entry", function_);
624 builder_->SetInsertPoint(compute_entry);
625 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
626 builder_->CreateRet(ConstInt32(0));
627 builder_->SetInsertPoint(compute_call_end);
628}
629
630CodeGenLLVM::TypedPointer CodeGenCPU::PackClosureData(const Array<Var>& vfields,
631 uint64_t* num_bytes,
632 std::string struct_name) {
633 if (vfields.size() == 0) {
634 *num_bytes = 0U;
635 return TypedPointer(t_void_p_, llvm::Constant::getNullValue(t_void_p_));
636 }
637 std::vector<llvm::Type*> fields;
638 for (Var v : vfields) {
639 auto it = var_map_.find(v.get());
640 ICHECK(it != var_map_.end());
641 fields.push_back(it->second->getType());
642 }
643 llvm::StructType* ctype = struct_name.size() ? llvm::StructType::create(fields, struct_name)
644 : llvm::StructType::create(fields);
645 llvm::AllocaInst* cvalue =
646 WithFunctionEntry([&]() { return builder_->CreateAlloca(ctype, ConstInt32(1)); });
647 llvm::Value* zero = ConstInt32(0);
648 for (size_t i = 0; i < vfields.size(); ++i) {
649 builder_->CreateStore(var_map_.at(vfields[i].get()),
650 builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(ctype, cvalue, {zero, ConstInt32(i)}));
651 }
652 *num_bytes = data_layout_->getTypeAllocSize(ctype);
653 return TypedPointer(ctype, cvalue);
654}
655
656void CodeGenCPU::UnpackClosureData(TypedPointer cdata, const Array<Var>& vfields,
657 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, llvm::Value*>* vmap) {
658 for (size_t i = 0; i < vfields.size(); ++i) {
659 llvm::Type* field_type = cdata.type->getStructElementType(i);
660 llvm::Value* field_addr =
661 builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(cdata.type, cdata.addr, {ConstInt32(0), ConstInt32(i)});
662 llvm::Value* load =
663 builder_->CreateLoad(field_type, field_addr, std::string(vfields[i]->name_hint));
664 (*vmap)[vfields[i].get()] = load;
665 }
666}
667
668void CodeGenCPU::CreateParallelLaunch(const Stmt& body, int num_task, std::string name) {
669 // closure data
670 llvm::Function* f =
671 llvm::Function::Create(ftype_tvm_parallel_lambda_, llvm::Function::PrivateLinkage,
672 "__tvm_parallel_lambda", module_.get());
673 SetTargetAttributes(f);
674
675 // allocate and setup the closure, call the closure.
676 Array<Var> vfields = tir::UndefinedVars(body, {});
677 uint64_t nbytes;
678 TypedPointer cdata = PackClosureData(vfields, &nbytes, "closure_" + name);
679#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 90
680 auto launch_callee = llvm::FunctionCallee(ftype_tvm_parallel_launch_, RuntimeTVMParallelLaunch());
681#else
682 auto launch_callee = RuntimeTVMParallelLaunch();
683#endif
684 llvm::BasicBlock* par_launch_end = CheckCallSuccess(builder_->CreateCall(
685 launch_callee,
686 {f, builder_->CreatePointerCast(cdata.addr, t_void_p_), ConstInt32(num_task)}));
687 // Setup the closure function.
688 auto* lambda_entry =
689 llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*llvm_target_->GetContext(), "parallel_closure_entry", f);
690 builder_->SetInsertPoint(lambda_entry);
691 auto it = f->arg_begin();
692 llvm::Value* task_id = &(*it++);
693 task_id->setName("task_id");
694 llvm::Value* penv = &(*it++);
695 cdata.addr = builder_->CreatePointerCast(&(*it++), cdata.addr->getType());
696 // setup new variable map, swap it with current var context.
697 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, llvm::Value*> new_vmap;
698 UnpackClosureData(cdata, vfields, &new_vmap);
699 // setup parallel env
700 ParallelEnv par_env;
701 par_env.task_id = Var("task_id", DataType::Int(32));
702 par_env.num_task = Var("num_task", DataType::Int(32));
703 new_vmap[par_env.task_id.get()] = task_id;
704 new_vmap[par_env.num_task.get()] = builder_->CreateLoad(
705 t_int32_,
706 builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(t_tvm_parallel_group_env_, penv, {ConstInt32(0), ConstInt32(1)}),
707 "num_task");
708 par_env.penv = penv;
709 auto new_analyzer = std::make_unique<arith::Analyzer>();
710 std::swap(function_, f);
711 std::swap(parallel_env_, par_env);
712 std::swap(analyzer_, new_analyzer);
713 std::swap(var_map_, new_vmap);
714 this->VisitStmt(body);
715 builder_->CreateRet(ConstInt32(0));
716 // swap the var map back, now we are back on track.
717 std::swap(var_map_, new_vmap);
718 std::swap(analyzer_, new_analyzer);
719 std::swap(parallel_env_, par_env);
720 std::swap(function_, f);
721 ICHECK_NE(par_env.parallel_loop_count, 0) << "Cannot find parallel loop within parallel launch";
722 builder_->SetInsertPoint(par_launch_end);
723}
724
725llvm::Value* CodeGenCPU::CreateStaticHandle() {
726 llvm::GlobalVariable* gv =
727 new llvm::GlobalVariable(*module_, t_void_p_, false, llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage,
728 nullptr, "__tvm_static_handle");
729#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 100
730 gv->setAlignment(llvm::Align(data_layout_->getTypeAllocSize(t_void_p_)));
731#else
732 gv->setAlignment(data_layout_->getTypeAllocSize(t_void_p_));
733#endif
734 gv->setInitializer(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(t_void_p_));
735 return gv;
736}
737
738void CodeGenCPU::CreateStaticInit(const std::string& init_fname, const Stmt& body) {
739 // closure data
740 llvm::Function* f =
741 llvm::Function::Create(ftype_tvm_static_init_callback_, llvm::Function::PrivateLinkage,
742 "__tvm_static_init_lambda", module_.get());
743 SetTargetAttributes(f);
744 llvm::Value* gv = CreateStaticHandle();
745 llvm::Function* finit = module_->getFunction(init_fname);
746 if (finit == nullptr) {
747 finit = llvm::Function::Create(ftype_tvm_static_init_, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
748 init_fname, module_.get());
749 }
750 // allocate and setup the closure, call the closure.
751 uint64_t nbytes;
752 Array<Var> vfields = tir::UndefinedVars(body, {});
753 TypedPointer cdata = PackClosureData(vfields, &nbytes);
754 llvm::BasicBlock* init_end = CheckCallSuccess(builder_->CreateCall(
755 finit, {gv, f, builder_->CreatePointerCast(cdata.addr, t_void_p_), ConstInt32(nbytes)}));
756 // Setup the closure function.
757 auto* lambda_entry = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*llvm_target_->GetContext(), "entry", f);
758 builder_->SetInsertPoint(lambda_entry);
759 auto it = f->arg_begin();
760 cdata.addr = builder_->CreatePointerCast(&(*it++), cdata.addr->getType());
761 // setup new variable map, swap it with current var context.
762 std::unordered_map<const VarNode*, llvm::Value*> new_vmap;
763 UnpackClosureData(cdata, vfields, &new_vmap);
764 ICHECK(parallel_env_.penv == nullptr);
765 auto new_analyzer = std::make_unique<arith::Analyzer>();
766 std::swap(function_, f);
767 std::swap(analyzer_, new_analyzer);
768 std::swap(var_map_, new_vmap);
769 this->VisitStmt(body);
770 builder_->CreateRet(ConstInt32(0));
771 // swap the var map back, now we are back on track.
772 std::swap(var_map_, new_vmap);
773 std::swap(analyzer_, new_analyzer);
774 std::swap(function_, f);
775 builder_->SetInsertPoint(init_end);
776}
777
778llvm::Value* CodeGenCPU::GetPackedFuncHandle(const std::string& fname) {
779 // We will store the packed function handle in global space.
780 // Initialize it during the first call.
781 llvm::DataLayout layout(module_.get());
782 uint64_t align = layout.getTypeAllocSize(t_tvm_func_handle_);
783 auto it = func_handle_map_.find(fname);
784
785 llvm::GlobalVariable* hptr;
786 if (it == func_handle_map_.end()) {
787 // create global location for the handle
788 // create the function handle
789 hptr =
790 new llvm::GlobalVariable(*module_, t_tvm_func_handle_, false,
791 llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage, nullptr, ".tvm_func." + fname);
792#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 100
793 hptr->setAlignment(llvm::Align(align));
794#else
795 hptr->setAlignment(align);
796#endif
797 hptr->setInitializer(llvm::Constant::getNullValue(t_tvm_func_handle_));
798 func_handle_map_[fname] = hptr;
799 } else {
800 hptr = it->second;
801 }
802 // create emit codes that checks and load the function.
803 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
804 llvm::BasicBlock* pre_block = builder_->GetInsertBlock();
805 auto* init_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "handle_init", function_);
806 auto* end_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "handle_init_end", function_);
807#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
808 llvm::Value* handle = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(hptr->getValueType(), hptr, llvm::Align(align));
809#elif TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 80
810 llvm::Value* handle = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(hptr->getValueType(), hptr, align);
811#else
812 llvm::Value* handle = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(hptr, align);
813#endif
814 llvm::Value* handle_not_null =
815 builder_->CreateICmpNE(handle, llvm::Constant::getNullValue(t_tvm_func_handle_));
816 builder_->CreateCondBr(handle_not_null, end_block, init_block, md_very_likely_branch_);
817 // Initialize the handle if needed.
818 builder_->SetInsertPoint(init_block);
819 llvm::Value* out =
820 WithFunctionEntry([&]() { return builder_->CreateAlloca(t_tvm_func_handle_); });
821#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
822 llvm::LoadInst* ctx_load = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(gv_mod_ctx_->getValueType(), gv_mod_ctx_,
823 llvm::Align(gv_mod_ctx_->getAlignment()));
824#elif TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 80
825 llvm::LoadInst* ctx_load = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(gv_mod_ctx_->getValueType(), gv_mod_ctx_,
826 gv_mod_ctx_->getAlignment());
827#else
828 llvm::LoadInst* ctx_load = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(gv_mod_ctx_, gv_mod_ctx_->getAlignment());
829#endif
830 ctx_load->setMetadata(
831 "tbaa", md_builder_->createTBAAStructTagNode(md_tbaa_ctx_ptr_, md_tbaa_ctx_ptr_, 0));
832#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 90
833 auto env_callee = llvm::FunctionCallee(ftype_tvm_get_func_from_env_, RuntimeTVMGetFuncFromEnv());
834#else
835 auto env_callee = RuntimeTVMGetFuncFromEnv();
836#endif
837 llvm::Value* retcode = builder_->CreateCall(env_callee, {ctx_load, GetConstString(fname), out});
838 init_block = CheckCallSuccess(retcode);
839#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
840 llvm::Value* loaded_handle =
841 builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(t_tvm_func_handle_, out, llvm::Align(align));
842#elif TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 80
843 llvm::Value* loaded_handle = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(t_tvm_func_handle_, out, align);
844#else
845 llvm::Value* loaded_handle = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(out, align);
846#endif
847 // Store the handle
848 builder_->CreateStore(loaded_handle, hptr);
849 builder_->CreateBr(end_block);
850 // end block
851 builder_->SetInsertPoint(end_block);
852 llvm::PHINode* phi = builder_->CreatePHI(t_tvm_func_handle_, 2);
853 phi->addIncoming(handle, pre_block);
854 phi->addIncoming(loaded_handle, init_block);
855 return phi;
856}
857
858CodeGenCPU::PackedCall CodeGenCPU::MakeCallPackedLowered(const Array<PrimExpr>& args,
859 const DataType& r_type,
860 const int64_t begin, const int64_t end,
861 bool use_string_lookup) {
862 PackedCall pc;
863 std::string func_name = args[0].as<StringImmNode>()->value;
864 // call the function
865 int64_t nargs = end - begin;
866 ICHECK_GE(nargs, 0);
867 llvm::Value* stack_value = MakeValue(args[1]);
868 llvm::Value* stack_tcode = MakeValue(args[2]);
869 llvm::Value* arg_value = builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(
870 t_tvm_value_, builder_->CreatePointerCast(stack_value, t_tvm_value_->getPointerTo()),
871 ConstInt32(begin));
872 TypedPointer arg_tcode =
873 CreateBufferPtr(stack_tcode, DataType::Int(32), {ConstInt32(begin)}, DataType::Int(32));
874 llvm::Value* ret_value = builder_->CreateInBoundsGEP(
875 t_tvm_value_, builder_->CreatePointerCast(stack_value, t_tvm_value_->getPointerTo()),
876 ConstInt32(end));
877 TypedPointer ret_tcode =
878 CreateBufferPtr(stack_tcode, DataType::Int(32), {ConstInt32(end)}, DataType::Int(32));
879
880 llvm::FunctionType* callee_ftype = nullptr;
881 llvm::Value* callee_value = nullptr;
882 std::vector<llvm::Value*> call_args;
883
884 if (use_string_lookup) {
885 callee_ftype = ftype_tvm_func_call_;
886 callee_value = RuntimeTVMFuncCall();
887 call_args.push_back(GetPackedFuncHandle(func_name));
888 call_args.insert(call_args.end(),
889 {arg_value, arg_tcode.addr, ConstInt32(nargs), ret_value, ret_tcode.addr});
890 } else {
891 callee_ftype = ftype_tvm_backend_packed_c_func_;
892 callee_value = module_->getFunction(func_name);
893 if (callee_value == nullptr) {
894 callee_value =
895 llvm::Function::Create(ftype_tvm_backend_packed_c_func_, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
896 func_name, module_.get());
897 }
898
899 nargs -= 1;
900 call_args.insert(call_args.end(), {
901 builder_->CreateBitCast(arg_value, t_void_p_),
902 arg_tcode.addr,
903 ConstInt32(nargs),
904 builder_->CreateBitCast(ret_value, t_void_p_),
905 ret_tcode.addr,
906 });
907 call_args.push_back(llvm::ConstantPointerNull::get(t_void_p_));
908 }
909#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 90
910 auto call_callee = llvm::FunctionCallee(callee_ftype, callee_value);
911#else
912 (void)callee_ftype; // use callee_ftype to avoid unused variable warning when using older LLVM.
913 auto call_callee = callee_value;
914#endif
915 llvm::Value* call = builder_->CreateCall(call_callee, call_args);
916
917 llvm::BasicBlock* end_block = CheckCallSuccess(call);
918
919 // Load the return value and cast it to the designated type (r_type).
920 DataType r_api_type = tir::APIType(r_type);
921 llvm::Type* llvm_r_api_type = DTypeToLLVMType(r_api_type);
922 llvm::Value* load_ptr = builder_->CreatePointerCast(ret_value, llvm_r_api_type->getPointerTo());
923#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
924 llvm::Value* rvalue = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(llvm_r_api_type, load_ptr, llvm::Align(8));
925#elif TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 80
926 llvm::Value* rvalue = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(llvm_r_api_type, load_ptr, 8);
927#else
928 llvm::Value* rvalue = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(load_ptr, 8);
929#endif
930 pc.ret_value = CreateCast(r_api_type, r_type, rvalue);
931
932 // Load the return type code.
933#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 110
934 pc.ret_tcode = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(ret_tcode.type, ret_tcode.addr, llvm::Align(8));
935#elif TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 80
936 pc.ret_tcode = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(ret_tcode.type, ret_tcode.addr, 8);
937#else
938 pc.ret_tcode = builder_->CreateAlignedLoad(ret_tcode.addr, 8);
939#endif
940
941 pc.end_block = end_block;
942 return pc;
943}
944
945llvm::Value* CodeGenCPU::CreateCallPacked(const CallNode* op, bool use_string_lookup) {
946 auto expected_num_args = use_string_lookup ? 5U : 6U;
947 ICHECK_EQ(op->args.size(), expected_num_args);
948 PackedCall pc = MakeCallPackedLowered(op->args, op->dtype, op->args[3].as<IntImmNode>()->value,
949 op->args[4].as<IntImmNode>()->value, use_string_lookup);
950 return pc.ret_value;
951}
952
953llvm::Value* CodeGenCPU::CreateCallTracePacked(const CallNode* op) {
954 ICHECK_EQ(op->args.size(), 6U);
955 PackedCall pc = MakeCallPackedLowered(op->args, op->dtype, op->args[3].as<IntImmNode>()->value,
956 op->args[4].as<IntImmNode>()->value, true);
957 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
958 // Get traced value.
959 llvm::Value* traced_value = MakeValue(op->args[5]);
960 // The update_block handles case when we need to update the return value.
961 llvm::BasicBlock* update_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "update_block", function_);
962 // The continue_block handles case when we need to return original
963 // traced value.
964 llvm::BasicBlock* continue_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "continue_block", function_);
965
966 // Check the ret_type_code and create cmp instruction.
967 llvm::Value* cmp =
968 builder_->CreateICmpNE(pc.ret_tcode, llvm::ConstantInt::get(t_int_, kTVMNullptr));
969 builder_->CreateCondBr(cmp, update_block, continue_block);
970 builder_->SetInsertPoint(update_block);
971 builder_->CreateBr(continue_block);
972 builder_->SetInsertPoint(continue_block);
973 // The return value depends on from what bb we come from.
974 llvm::PHINode* phi_rvalue = builder_->CreatePHI(traced_value->getType(), 2);
975 phi_rvalue->addIncoming(pc.ret_value, update_block);
976 phi_rvalue->addIncoming(traced_value, pc.end_block);
977 return phi_rvalue;
978}
979
980llvm::Value* CodeGenCPU::RuntimeTVMFuncCall() {
981 if (f_tvm_func_call_ != nullptr) return f_tvm_func_call_;
982 return GetContextPtr(gv_tvm_func_call_);
983}
984
985llvm::Value* CodeGenCPU::RuntimeTVMGetFuncFromEnv() {
986 if (f_tvm_get_func_from_env_ != nullptr) return f_tvm_get_func_from_env_;
987 return GetContextPtr(gv_tvm_get_func_from_env_);
988}
989llvm::Value* CodeGenCPU::RuntimeTVMAPISetLastError() {
990 if (f_tvm_api_set_last_error_ != nullptr) return f_tvm_api_set_last_error_;
991 return GetContextPtr(gv_tvm_api_set_last_error_);
992}
993llvm::Value* CodeGenCPU::RuntimeTVMParallelLaunch() {
994 if (f_tvm_parallel_launch_ != nullptr) return f_tvm_parallel_launch_;
995 return GetContextPtr(gv_tvm_parallel_launch_);
996}
997
998llvm::Value* CodeGenCPU::RuntimeTVMParallelBarrier() {
999 if (f_tvm_parallel_barrier_ != nullptr) return f_tvm_parallel_barrier_;
1000 return GetContextPtr(gv_tvm_parallel_barrier_);
1001}
1002
1003/*! \brief Defines LLVM Types for each Metadata member type. */
1004struct MetadataLlvmTypes {
1005 llvm::Type* t_float64;
1006 llvm::Type* t_uint8;
1007 llvm::Type* t_int64;
1008 llvm::Type* t_bool;
1009 llvm::Type* t_cstring;
1010 llvm::Type* t_void_p;
1011 llvm::StructType* t_data_type;
1012
1013 /*! \brief Maps a MetadataBase subclass' type_key to its corresponding LLVM StructType. */
1014 ::std::unordered_map<std::string, llvm::StructType*> structs_by_type_key;
1015};
1016
1017class MetadataTypeDefiner : public AttrVisitor {
1018 public:
1019 MetadataTypeDefiner(llvm::LLVMContext* ctx, struct MetadataLlvmTypes* llvm_types)
1020 : ctx_{ctx}, llvm_types_{llvm_types} {}
1021
1022 void Visit(const char* key, double* value) final {
1023 elements_.emplace_back(llvm_types_->t_float64);
1024 }
1025 void Visit(const char* key, int64_t* value) final {
1026 elements_.emplace_back(llvm_types_->t_int64);
1027 }
1028 void Visit(const char* key, uint64_t* value) final {
1029 elements_.emplace_back(llvm_types_->t_int64);
1030 }
1031 void Visit(const char* key, int* value) final { elements_.emplace_back(llvm_types_->t_int64); }
1032 void Visit(const char* key, bool* value) final { elements_.emplace_back(llvm_types_->t_bool); }
1033 void Visit(const char* key, std::string* value) final {
1034 elements_.emplace_back(llvm_types_->t_cstring);
1035 }
1036 void Visit(const char* key, void** value) final { elements_.emplace_back(llvm_types_->t_void_p); }
1037 void Visit(const char* key, DataType* value) final {
1038 elements_.emplace_back(llvm_types_->t_data_type);
1039 }
1040 void Visit(const char* key, runtime::NDArray* value) final {
1041 elements_.emplace_back(llvm_types_->t_int64);
1042 elements_.emplace_back(llvm_types_->t_void_p);
1043 }
1044
1045 private:
1046 void VisitMetadataBase(runtime::metadata::MetadataBase metadata) {
1047 elements_.emplace_back(llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(
1048 llvm::StructType::create(*ctx_, metadata->get_c_struct_name())));
1049 if (visited_.find(metadata->get_c_struct_name()) != visited_.end()) {
1050 return;
1051 }
1052
1053 if (to_visit_.find(metadata->get_c_struct_name()) != to_visit_.end()) {
1054 return;
1055 }
1056 to_visit_[metadata->get_c_struct_name()] = metadata;
1057 }
1058
1059 public:
1060 using MetadataKind = runtime::metadata::MetadataKind;
1061
1062 void VisitArray(const runtime::metadata::MetadataArrayNode* arr) {
1063 switch (arr->kind) {
1064 case MetadataKind::kUint64: // LLVM encodes signed and unsigned with same types.
1065 case MetadataKind::kInt64:
1066 elements_.emplace_back(llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(llvm_types_->t_int64));
1067 break;
1068 case MetadataKind::kBool:
1069 elements_.emplace_back(llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(llvm_types_->t_bool));
1070 break;
1071 case MetadataKind::kString:
1072 elements_.emplace_back(llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(llvm_types_->t_cstring));
1073 break;
1074 case MetadataKind::kHandle:
1075 CHECK(false) << "Do not support handle";
1076 break;
1077 case MetadataKind::kMetadata:
1078 if (llvm_types_->structs_by_type_key.count(arr->type_key)) {
1079 elements_.emplace_back(
1080 llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(llvm_types_->structs_by_type_key[arr->type_key]));
1081 }
1082 break;
1083 default:
1084 CHECK(false) << "Unsupported metadata kind " << arr->kind;
1085 break;
1086 }
1087 }
1088
1089 void Visit(const char* key, ObjectRef* value) final {
1090 const runtime::metadata::MetadataArrayNode* arr =
1091 value->as<runtime::metadata::MetadataArrayNode>();
1092 if (arr != nullptr) {
1093 VisitArray(arr);
1094 } else {
1095 elements_.emplace_back(
1096 llvm::PointerType::getUnqual(llvm_types_->structs_by_type_key[(*value)->GetTypeKey()]));
1097 }
1098 }
1099
1100 void DefineType(runtime::metadata::MetadataBase metadata) {
1101 ICHECK(elements_.empty());
1102 ReflectionVTable::Global()->VisitAttrs(metadata.operator->(), this);
1103 llvm_types_->structs_by_type_key[metadata->GetTypeKey()] =
1104 llvm::StructType::create(*ctx_, elements_, metadata->get_c_struct_name());
1105 elements_.clear();
1106 }
1107
1108 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx_;
1109 struct MetadataLlvmTypes* llvm_types_;
1110 ::std::unordered_set<::std::string> visited_;
1111 ::std::unordered_map<::std::string, runtime::metadata::MetadataBase> to_visit_;
1112 ::std::vector<llvm::Type*> elements_;
1113};
1114
1115class MetadataSerializerLLVM : public AttrVisitor {
1116 using MetadataKind = runtime::metadata::MetadataKind;
1117
1118 public:
1119 MetadataSerializerLLVM(CodeGenLLVM* codegen, struct MetadataLlvmTypes* llvm_types)
1120 : codegen_{codegen}, llvm_types_{llvm_types} {}
1121
1122 void Visit(const char* key, double* value) final {
1123 elements_.back().emplace_back(llvm::ConstantFP::get(llvm_types_->t_float64, *value));
1124 }
1125 void Visit(const char* key, int64_t* value) final {
1126 elements_.back().emplace_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
1127 llvm_types_->t_int64, static_cast<uint64_t>(*value), true /* isSigned */));
1128 }
1129 void Visit(const char* key, uint64_t* value) final {
1130 elements_.back().emplace_back(
1131 llvm::ConstantInt::get(llvm_types_->t_int64, *value, false /* isSigned */));
1132 }
1133 void Visit(const char* key, int* value) final {
1134 elements_.back().emplace_back(
1135 llvm::ConstantInt::get(llvm_types_->t_int64, *value, true /* isSigned */));
1136 }
1137 void Visit(const char* key, bool* value) final {
1138 elements_.back().emplace_back(llvm::ConstantInt::get(
1139 llvm_types_->t_uint8, static_cast<uint64_t>(*value), false /* isSigned */));
1140 }
1141 void Visit(const char* key, std::string* value) final {
1142 elements_.back().emplace_back(codegen_->GetConstString(*value));
1143 }
1144 void Visit(const char* key, void** value) final {
1145 CHECK(false) << "Do not support serializing void*";
1146 }
1147 void Visit(const char* key, DataType* value) final {
1148 elements_.back().emplace_back(llvm::ConstantStruct::get(
1149 llvm_types_->t_data_type,
1150 {llvm::ConstantInt::get(llvm_types_->t_uint8, value->code(), false /* isSigned */),
1151 llvm::ConstantInt::get(llvm_types_->t_uint8, value->bits(), false /* isSigned */),
1152 llvm::ConstantInt::get(llvm_types_->t_uint8, value->lanes(), false /* isSigned */)}));
1153 }
1154
1155 // Serializing NDArray as tuple of len, data
1156 void Visit(const char* key, runtime::NDArray* value) final {
1157 std::string bytes;
1158 dmlc::MemoryStringStream stream(&bytes);
1159 value->Save(&stream);
1160 elements_.back().emplace_back(
1161 llvm::ConstantInt::get(llvm_types_->t_int64, bytes.length(), true /* isSigned */));
1162 elements_.back().emplace_back(codegen_->GetConstString(bytes));
1163 }
1164
1165 void VisitMetadata(runtime::metadata::MetadataBase metadata) {
1166 elements_.emplace_back(std::vector<llvm::Constant*>());
1167 ReflectionVTable::Global()->VisitAttrs(metadata.operator->(), this);
1168 auto struct_elements = elements_.back();
1169 elements_.pop_back();
1170 auto struct_ty = llvm_types_->structs_by_type_key[metadata->GetTypeKey()];
1171 ICHECK(struct_ty != nullptr) << "Did not find LLVM StructType* for type_key="
1172 << metadata->GetTypeKey();
1173 CHECK_EQ(struct_elements.size(), struct_ty->getNumElements());
1174 auto out = llvm::ConstantStruct::get(struct_ty, struct_elements);
1175 if (elements_.size() > 0) {
1176 elements_.back().push_back(out);
1177 } else {
1178 last_production_ = out;
1179 }
1180 }
1181
1182 void VisitArray(const runtime::metadata::MetadataArrayNode* arr) {
1183 llvm::Type* element_type;
1184 switch (arr->kind) {
1185 case MetadataKind::kInt64:
1186 element_type = llvm_types_->t_int64;
1187 break;
1188 case MetadataKind::kUint64:
1189 element_type = llvm_types_->t_int64;
1190 break;
1191 case MetadataKind::kBool:
1192 element_type = llvm_types_->t_uint8;
1193 break;
1194 case MetadataKind::kString:
1195 element_type = llvm_types_->t_cstring;
1196 break;
1197 case MetadataKind::kMetadata: {
1198 element_type = llvm_types_->structs_by_type_key[arr->type_key];
1199 ICHECK(element_type != nullptr)
1200 << "Did not find LLVM StructType* for type_key=" << arr->type_key;
1201 break;
1202 }
1203 default:
1204 LOG(FATAL) << "unknown metadata kind " << arr->kind;
1205 break;
1206 }
1207
1208 elements_.emplace_back(std::vector<llvm::Constant*>());
1209 for (auto o : arr->array) {
1210 if (o->IsInstance<FloatImmNode>()) {
1211 double value = Downcast<FloatImm>(o)->value;
1212 Visit(nullptr, &value);
1213 }
1214 if (o->IsInstance<IntImmNode>()) {
1215 auto value = Downcast<IntImm>(o)->value;
1216 Visit(nullptr, &value);
1217 } else if (o->IsInstance<StringObj>()) {
1218 ::std::string value = Downcast<String>(o);
1219 Visit(nullptr, &value);
1220 } else {
1221 // nested array not possible.
1222 VisitMetadata(Downcast<runtime::metadata::MetadataBase>(o));
1223 }
1224 }
1225 auto array = elements_.back();
1226 elements_.pop_back();
1227 CHECK(element_type != nullptr);
1228 auto arr_ty = llvm::ArrayType::get(element_type, array.size());
1229 auto llvm_arr = llvm::ConstantArray::get(arr_ty, array);
1230
1231 if (elements_.size() > 0) {
1232 elements_.back().emplace_back(
1233 codegen_->GetGlobalConstant(llvm_arr, "", llvm::GlobalValue::PrivateLinkage));
1234 } else {
1235 last_production_ = llvm_arr;
1236 }
1237 }
1238
1239 void Visit(const char* key, ObjectRef* value) final {
1240 const runtime::metadata::MetadataArrayNode* arr =
1241 value->as<runtime::metadata::MetadataArrayNode>();
1242 if (arr != nullptr) {
1243 VisitArray(arr);
1244 return;
1245 }
1246
1247 runtime::metadata::MetadataBase metadata = Downcast<runtime::metadata::MetadataBase>(*value);
1248 VisitMetadata(metadata);
1249 }
1250
1251 llvm::Constant* Serialize(runtime::metadata::MetadataBase metadata) {
1252 Visit(nullptr, &metadata);
1253 ICHECK(last_production_);
1254 return codegen_->GetGlobalConstant(last_production_);
1255 }
1256
1257 CodeGenLLVM* codegen_;
1258 MetadataLlvmTypes* llvm_types_;
1259 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx_;
1260 llvm::Module* module_;
1261 std::vector<std::vector<llvm::Constant*>> elements_;
1262 llvm::Constant* last_production_;
1263};
1264
1265void CodeGenCPU::DefineMetadata(runtime::metadata::Metadata metadata) {
1266 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
1267 MetadataLlvmTypes llvm_types{
1268 t_float64_ /* t_float64 */,
1269 llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(*ctx) /* t_uint8 */,
1270 t_int64_ /* t_int64 */,
1271 llvm::Type::getInt8Ty(*ctx) /* t_bool */,
1272 t_char_->getPointerTo() /* t_cstring */,
1273 t_void_p_ /* t_void_p */,
1274 llvm::StructType::create(*ctx, {t_int8_, t_int8_, t_int8_}, "DLDataType") /* t_data_type */,
1275 };
1276
1277 // create sample ConstantInfoMetadata instance for MetadataTypeDefiner
1278 std::string bytes;
1279 runtime::NDArray ci = runtime::NDArray::Empty({0}, DataType::UInt(8), Device{kDLCPU});
1280 dmlc::MemoryStringStream stream(&bytes);
1281 ci.Save(&stream);
1282 TVMConstantInfo di =
1283 TVMConstantInfo{"default-none", 0, static_cast<int64_t>(bytes.size()), bytes.c_str()};
1284
1285 std::vector<runtime::metadata::MetadataBase> queue;
1286 queue.push_back(runtime::metadata::ConstantInfoMetadata(&di));
1287
1288 metadata::DiscoverComplexTypesVisitor discover_complex{&queue};
1289 discover_complex.Discover(metadata);
1290
1291 MetadataTypeDefiner definer{ctx, &llvm_types};
1292 for (auto md : queue) {
1293 if (md.defined()) {
1294 definer.DefineType(md);
1295 }
1296 }
1297
1298 MetadataSerializerLLVM serializer{this, &llvm_types};
1299 auto metadata_constant_gv = serializer.Serialize(metadata);
1300
1301 function_ =
1302 llvm::Function::Create(ftype_tvm_backend_packed_c_func_, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
1303 runtime::symbol::tvm_get_c_metadata, module_.get());
1304 SetTargetAttributes(function_);
1305 function_->setCallingConv(llvm::CallingConv::C);
1306 function_->setDLLStorageClass(llvm::GlobalValue::DLLStorageClassTypes::DLLExportStorageClass);
1307
1308 llvm::BasicBlock* entry_point_entry = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "entry", function_);
1309 builder_->SetInsertPoint(entry_point_entry);
1310
1311 auto ret_values_p = builder_->CreateBitCast(GetArg(function_, 3), t_void_p_->getPointerTo());
1312 builder_->CreateStore(builder_->CreateBitCast(metadata_constant_gv, t_void_p_), ret_values_p);
1313
1314 auto ret_tcode = builder_->CreateBitCast(GetArg(function_, 4), t_int_->getPointerTo());
1315 builder_->CreateStore(llvm::ConstantInt::get(t_int_, kTVMOpaqueHandle), ret_tcode);
1316
1317 builder_->CreateRet(ConstInt32(0));
1318}
1319
1320void CodeGenCPU::DefineFunctionRegistry(Array<String> func_names) {
1321 ICHECK(is_system_lib_) << "Loading of --system-lib modules is yet to be defined for C runtime";
1322 Array<String> symbols;
1323 std::vector<llvm::Constant*> funcs;
1324 for (auto sym : func_names) {
1325 symbols.push_back(sym);
1326 auto* sym_func =
1327 llvm::Function::Create(ftype_tvm_backend_packed_c_func_, llvm::GlobalValue::ExternalLinkage,
1328 sym.operator std::string(), module_.get());
1329
1330 funcs.emplace_back(sym_func);
1331 }
1332 llvm::ArrayType* t_tvm_crt_func_ptrs =
1333 llvm::ArrayType::get(ftype_tvm_backend_packed_c_func_->getPointerTo(), funcs.size());
1334 llvm::DataLayout layout(module_.get());
1335
1336 llvm::GlobalVariable* func_registry_ptrs = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
1337 *module_, t_tvm_crt_func_ptrs, true, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
1338 llvm::ConstantArray::get(t_tvm_crt_func_ptrs, funcs), "_tvm_func_registry_ptrs");
1339
1340 uint64_t align = layout.getTypeAllocSize(ftype_tvm_backend_packed_c_func_->getPointerTo());
1341#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 100
1342 func_registry_ptrs->setAlignment(llvm::Align(align));
1343#else
1344 func_registry_ptrs->setAlignment(align);
1345#endif
1346 llvm::GlobalVariable* func_registry = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
1347 *module_, t_tvm_crt_func_registry_, true, llvm::GlobalVariable::InternalLinkage,
1348 llvm::ConstantStruct::get(
1349 t_tvm_crt_func_registry_,
1350 {GetConstString(::tvm::target::GenerateFuncRegistryNames(symbols)),
1351 llvm::ConstantExpr::getBitCast(func_registry_ptrs,
1352 ftype_tvm_backend_packed_c_func_->getPointerTo())}),
1353 "_tvm_crt_func_registry");
1354 llvm::GlobalVariable* module = new llvm::GlobalVariable(
1355 *module_, t_tvm_crt_module_, true, llvm::GlobalValue::InternalLinkage,
1356 llvm::ConstantStruct::get(t_tvm_crt_module_, {func_registry}), "_tvm_crt_module");
1357
1358 // Now build TVMSystemLibEntryPoint.
1359 llvm::FunctionType* ftype = llvm::FunctionType::get(t_void_p_, {}, false);
1360 function_ = llvm::Function::Create(ftype, llvm::Function::ExternalLinkage,
1361 "TVMSystemLibEntryPoint", module_.get());
1362 SetTargetAttributes(function_);
1363 llvm::BasicBlock* entry_point_entry =
1364 llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*llvm_target_->GetContext(), "entry", function_);
1365 builder_->SetInsertPoint(entry_point_entry);
1366 builder_->CreateRet(builder_->CreateBitCast(module, t_void_p_));
1367}
1368
1369void CodeGenCPU::AddStartupFunction() {
1370 if (!target_c_runtime_) {
1371 llvm::FunctionType* ftype = llvm::FunctionType::get(t_void_, {}, false);
1372 function_ = llvm::Function::Create(ftype, llvm::Function::InternalLinkage,
1373 "__tvm_module_startup", module_.get());
1374 SetTargetAttributes(function_);
1375 llvm::BasicBlock* startup_entry =
1376 llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*llvm_target_->GetContext(), "entry", function_);
1377 builder_->SetInsertPoint(startup_entry);
1378 for (const auto& kv : export_system_symbols_) {
1379 llvm::Value* name = GetConstString(kv.first);
1380 builder_->CreateCall(f_tvm_register_system_symbol_,
1381 {name, builder_->CreateBitCast(kv.second, t_void_p_)});
1382 }
1383 llvm::appendToGlobalCtors(*module_, function_, 65535);
1384 builder_->CreateRet(nullptr);
1385 }
1386}
1387
1388llvm::Value* CodeGenCPU::CreateIntrinsic(const CallNode* op) {
1389 if (op->op.same_as(builtin::tvm_call_packed_lowered())) {
1390 return CreateCallPacked(op, true /* use_string_lookup */);
1391 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::tvm_call_trace_packed_lowered())) {
1392 return CreateCallTracePacked(op);
1393 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::tvm_call_cpacked_lowered())) {
1394 return CreateCallPacked(op, false /* use_string_lookup */);
1395 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::tvm_static_handle())) {
1396 return CreateStaticHandle();
1397 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::tvm_throw_last_error())) {
1398 builder_->CreateRet(ConstInt32(-1));
1399 auto next_block = std::next(builder_->GetInsertBlock()->getIterator());
1400 llvm::BasicBlock* new_bb =
1401 llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*llvm_target_->GetContext(), "cont", function_, &*next_block);
1402 builder_->SetInsertPoint(new_bb);
1403 return ConstInt32(-1);
1404 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::tvm_struct_get())) {
1405 ICHECK_EQ(op->args.size(), 3U);
1406 int kind = op->args[2].as<IntImmNode>()->value;
1407 TypedPointer ref =
1408 CreateStructRefPtr(op->dtype, MakeValue(op->args[0]), MakeValue(op->args[1]), kind);
1409 if (kind == builtin::kArrAddr) {
1410 return builder_->CreatePointerCast(ref.addr, t_void_p_);
1411 } else {
1412 return builder_->CreateLoad(ref.type, ref.addr);
1413 }
1414 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::tvm_struct_set())) {
1415 ICHECK_EQ(op->args.size(), 4U);
1416 int kind = op->args[2].as<IntImmNode>()->value;
1417 llvm::Value* value = MakeValue(op->args[3]);
1418 TypedPointer ref = CreateStructRefPtr(op->args[3].dtype(), MakeValue(op->args[0]),
1419 MakeValue(op->args[1]), kind);
1420 ICHECK(kind != builtin::kArrAddr);
1421 if (value->getType()->isPointerTy()) {
1422 value = builder_->CreatePointerCast(value, ref.type);
1423 }
1424 builder_->CreateStore(value, ref.addr);
1425 return ConstInt32(0);
1426 } else if (op->op.same_as(builtin::tvm_stack_alloca())) {
1427 ICHECK_EQ(op->args.size(), 2U);
1428 const std::string& type = op->args[0].as<StringImmNode>()->value;
1429 return WithFunctionEntry([&]() -> llvm::AllocaInst* {
1430 const int64_t* pval = as_const_int(op->args[1]);
1431 ICHECK(pval) << "require stack alloca to contain constant value";
1432 llvm::Value* num = ConstInt32(pval[0]);
1433 if (type == "shape") {
1434 return builder_->CreateAlloca(t_tvm_shape_index_, num);
1435 } else if (type == "arg_value") {
1436 return builder_->CreateAlloca(t_tvm_value_, num);
1437 } else if (type == "arg_tcode") {
1438 return builder_->CreateAlloca(t_int_, num);
1439 } else if (type == "array") {
1440 return builder_->CreateAlloca(t_tvm_array_, num);
1441 } else {
1442 LOG(FATAL) << "Unknown stack alloca type " << type;
1443 return nullptr;
1444 }
1445 });
1446 } else {
1447 return CodeGenLLVM::CreateIntrinsic(op);
1448 }
1449}
1450
1451void CodeGenCPU::VisitStmt_(const AssertStmtNode* op) {
1452 llvm::Value* cond = MakeValue(op->condition);
1453 std::ostringstream os;
1454 os << "Assert fail: " << op->condition;
1455 if (op->message.as<StringImmNode>()) {
1456 os << ", " << op->message.as<StringImmNode>()->value;
1457 }
1458 llvm::Value* msg = GetConstString(os.str());
1459 llvm::LLVMContext* ctx = llvm_target_->GetContext();
1460 auto* fail_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "assert_fail", function_);
1461 auto* end_block = llvm::BasicBlock::Create(*ctx, "assert_end", function_);
1462 builder_->CreateCondBr(cond, end_block, fail_block, md_very_likely_branch_);
1463 // fail condition.
1464 builder_->SetInsertPoint(fail_block);
1465
1466#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 90
1467 auto err_callee =
1468 llvm::FunctionCallee(ftype_tvm_api_set_last_error_, RuntimeTVMAPISetLastError());
1469#else
1470 auto err_callee = RuntimeTVMAPISetLastError();
1471#endif
1472 builder_->CreateCall(err_callee, {msg});
1473 builder_->CreateRet(ConstInt32(-1));
1474 // otherwise set it to be new end.
1475 builder_->SetInsertPoint(end_block);
1476 CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(op);
1477}
1478
1479void CodeGenCPU::VisitStmt_(const AttrStmtNode* op) {
1480 if (op->attr_key == tir::attr::coproc_uop_scope) {
1481 const StringImmNode* value = op->value.as<StringImmNode>();
1482 ICHECK(value != nullptr);
1483 this->CreateStaticInit(value->value, op->body);
1484 } else if (op->attr_key == tir::attr::compute_scope) {
1485 this->CreateComputeScope(op);
1486 } else if (tir::attr::IsPragmaKey(op->attr_key)) {
1487 if (op->attr_key == "pragma_parallel_stride_pattern") {
1488 ICHECK(parallel_env_.penv != nullptr)
1489 << "Pragma parallel_stride_pattern only valid in parallel launch";
1490 parallel_env_.stride_pattern = true;
1491 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1492 } else if (op->attr_key == "pragma_parallel_launch_point") {
1493 CreateParallelLaunch(op->body, 0, "pragma_parallel");
1494 } else if (op->attr_key == "pragma_parallel_barrier_when_finish") {
1495 ICHECK(parallel_env_.penv != nullptr) << "Cannot run barrier without parallel environment";
1496 ICHECK(!parallel_env_.in_parallel_loop)
1497 << "Cannot not place within parallel loop as the workload may differ, "
1498 << " place it between parallel and parallel_launch_point";
1499 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1500#if TVM_LLVM_VERSION >= 90
1501 auto bar_callee =
1502 llvm::FunctionCallee(ftype_tvm_parallel_barrier_, RuntimeTVMParallelBarrier());
1503#else
1504 auto bar_callee = RuntimeTVMParallelBarrier();
1505#endif
1506 builder_->CreateCall(bar_callee, {MakeValue(parallel_env_.task_id), parallel_env_.penv});
1507 } else if (op->attr_key == tir::attr::pragma_import_llvm) {
1508 const StringImmNode* value = op->value.as<StringImmNode>();
1509 ICHECK(value != nullptr);
1510 this->HandleImport(value->value);
1511 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1512 } else {
1513 LOG(WARNING) << "Unknown pragma " << op->attr_key;
1514 this->VisitStmt(op->body);
1515 }
1516 } else {
1517 CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(op);
1518 }
1519}
1520
1521void CodeGenCPU::VisitStmt_(const ForNode* op) {
1522 ICHECK(is_zero(op->min));
1523 if (op->kind == ForKind::kSerial || op->kind == ForKind::kUnrolled) {
1524 CodeGenLLVM::VisitStmt_(op);
1525 } else if (op->kind == ForKind::kParallel) {
1526 if (parallel_env_.penv == nullptr) {
1527 CreateParallelLaunch(For(op->loop_var, op->min, op->extent, op->kind, op->body,
1528 op->thread_binding, op->annotations),
1529 0, std::string("loop_parallel_") + op->loop_var->name_hint.c_str());
1530 } else {
1531 // already in parallel env.
1532 ICHECK(parallel_env_.task_id.defined());
1533 ICHECK(parallel_env_.num_task.defined());
1534 ICHECK(parallel_env_.penv != nullptr);
1535 DataType t = op->extent.dtype();
1536 PrimExpr num_task = cast(t, parallel_env_.num_task);
1537 PrimExpr task_id = cast(t, parallel_env_.task_id);
1538 ICHECK(!parallel_env_.in_parallel_loop)
1539 << "Nested parallel loop is not supported by threadpool, try fuse them instead";
1540 parallel_env_.in_parallel_loop = true;
1541 if (parallel_env_.stride_pattern) {
1542 CreateSerialFor(MakeValue(task_id), MakeValue(op->extent), MakeValue(num_task),
1543 op->loop_var, op->body);
1544 } else {
1545 PrimExpr step = (op->extent + num_task - make_const(t, 1)) / num_task;
1546 PrimExpr begin = min(task_id * step, op->extent);
1547 PrimExpr end = min((task_id + make_const(t, 1)) * step, op->extent);
1548 CreateSerialFor(MakeValue(begin), MakeValue(end),
1549 llvm::ConstantInt::getSigned(GetLLVMType(end), 1), op->loop_var, op->body);
1550 }
1551 parallel_env_.in_parallel_loop = false;
1552 ++parallel_env_.parallel_loop_count;
1553 }
1554 } else {
1555 LOG(FATAL) << "cannot handle for type " << op->kind;
1556 }
1557}
1558
1559TVM_REGISTER_GLOBAL("tvm.codegen.llvm.target_cpu")
1560 .set_body([](const TVMArgs& targs, TVMRetValue* rv) {
1561 *rv = static_cast<void*>(new CodeGenCPU());
1562 });
